ya I was talking about greasing just the wiper shafts (that go through 
the body/brass bushings).  anti-sieze worked for me for that 
purpose--maybe graphite better. . . perhaps the motor needs oil too (not 
grease?) but I didn't need to get that far in.

Will A.
> And watch what grease you use if you're in a cold climate. I used 
> synthetic grease in my VW bug wiper motor, and it is too thick, and 
> causes the motor to "lug". I would suggest a good graphite/oil lube 
> instead of grease. I had to dismantle the motor after I had greased 
> it, and it ran almost twice as fast after using the graphite/oil lube.
